{"id": "112458", "title": "Bug 112458: Property Editor still shows the properties of layout items when switched to Master page viewer.", "description": "The Property Editor still shows the properties of layout items when switched to the Master page viewer.", "OB": "When switching to the Master Page viewer, the Property Editor does not change to reflect the Master Page properties.", "EB": "When switching to the Master Page viewer, the Property Editor should change to reflect the Master Page properties.", "SR": "To reproduce the issue: 
1. Create a new report and insert a label.
2. Select the label. (The Property Editor shows the label's properties)
3. Switch to the Master Page viewer and observe the Property Editor; it should show the Master Page properties but instead, it still shows the label's properties."}
